{
  "ProofStructure": [
    {
      "type": "Define",
      "symbol": "f",
      "meaning": [
        "f(x) = \\sqrt{x(1 - x)}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Show",
      "proposition": [
        "f(x) = \\sqrt{x(1 - x)} is continuous on the closed interval [0, 1]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Fix",
      "var_list": [
        "x_0"
      ],
      "condition": [
        "x_0 \\in (0, 1)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Define",
      "symbol": "\\eta",
      "meaning": [
        "\\eta = \\min\\{x_0, 1 - x_0\\}",
        "\\eta > 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "When $|x - x_0| < \\eta$ and $x \\in (0, 1)$, we have $| \\sqrt{x(1 - x)} - \\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)} | = \\frac{|(1 - x) - (1 - x_0)| |x - x_0|}{\\sqrt{x(1 - x)} + \\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)}} < \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)}} |x - x_0|."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Fix",
      "var_list": [
        "\\epsilon"
      ],
      "condition": [
        "\\epsilon > 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Define",
      "symbol": "\\delta",
      "meaning": [
        "\\delta = \\min\\{ \\eta, \\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)}\\, \\epsilon \\}"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "When $|x - x_0| < \\delta$, we have $| \\sqrt{x(1 - x)} - \\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)} | < \\frac{1}{\\sqrt{x_0(1 - x_0)}} |x - x_0| < \\epsilon$."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "Therefore, $f(x) = \\sqrt{x(1 - x)}$ is continuous on $(0, 1)$."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Hint",
      "comment": "Now consider the endpoints."
    },
    {
      "type": "Fix",
      "var_list": [
        "\\epsilon"
      ],
      "condition": [
        "\\epsilon > 0"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Define",
      "symbol": "\\delta",
      "meaning": [
        "\\delta = \\epsilon^2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "When $0 \\leq x < \\delta$, $| f(x) - f(0) | \\leq \\sqrt{x} < \\epsilon$."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "And when $1 - \\delta < x \\leq 1$, $| f(x) - f(1) | \\leq \\sqrt{1 - x} < \\epsilon$."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "This shows that $f(x)$ is continuous at $x = 0$ from the right and at $x = 1$ from the left."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    },
    {
      "type": "Have",
      "proposition": [
        "Thus, $f(x) = \\sqrt{x(1 - x)}$ is continuous on the closed interval $[0, 1]$."
      ],
      "reasons": []
    }
  ]
}